crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The analyzed binary is a sophisticated Windows infostealer/RAT. It avoids static detection by maintaining a minimal import table and dynamically resolving its functional APIs at runtime via LoadLibraryA and GetProcAddress. Key malicious behaviors identified include: 1) Screen Capture: Function sub_404255 manually constructs BMP files (evidenced by the 0x4d42 'BM' header) for exfiltration. 2) C2 Communication: Function sub_4031ee implements an HTTP POST-based command and control mechanism, formatting stolen data into key-value pairs. 3) Cryptography: A custom Base64 implementation is present in sub_4012a4, used alongside various string decryption routines (sub_4016d5) to mask internal strings and exfiltrated data. 4) Information Gathering: The malware recursively traverses the file system (sub_4067ad), enumerates processes, and interacts with the registry (HKCU) to harvest system and user information. Anti-analysis checks, including OS version validation and environment sensing, are performed before the payload execution.
